title: Directory status (file count and freshness)
agents: linux
catalog: os/files
license: GPL-2.0-or-later
distribution: check_mk
description:
 The check monitors configured directories on Linux hosts. For each directory it
 reports the number of regular files (non-recursive) and the age of the newest
 file (based on modification time).

 Thresholds for the maximum number of files and the maximum age of the newest
 file can be configured via the WATO ruleset
 {Directory status (file count and freshness)}.

 Directories to monitor are configured via the agent bakery ruleset
 {Directory status (Linux)} or by placing paths in
 {$MK_CONFDIR}/directory_status.cfg on the host.

item:
 Absolute path of the monitored directory.

discovery:
 One service is created for each directory reported by the agent plug-in.
